#: ../../../blog/posts/2025-07-26-numpy-build-error.rst:7
msgid "Poetry環境でのnumpyビルドエラーとバージョン制約による解決メモ"
msgstr ""
"numpy build error in Poetry environment and resolution notes due to version "
"constraints"

#: ../../../blog/posts/2025-07-26-numpy-build-error.rst:9
msgid ""
"Windows上で、Gitから取得したPythonプロジェクトを `poetry install` した際に、`numpy` "
"のビルドに失敗する事象に遭遇した。Poetry環境でのエラーでありながら、原因は `numpy` のビルド処理にあった。"
msgstr ""
"When I tried `poetry install` on a Python project obtained from Git on "
"Windows, I encountered an issue where `numpy` build failed. Although the "
"error occurred in the Poetry environment, the cause was in the `numpy` build"
" process."

#: ../../../blog/posts/2025-07-26-numpy-build-error.rst:11
msgid "以下に、再現環境と解決までの経緯を記録しておく。"
msgstr ""
"Below is a record of the reproduction environment and the process leading up"
" to the resolution."

#: ../../../blog/posts/2025-07-26-numpy-build-error.rst:14
msgid "事象概要"
msgstr "Event summary"

#: ../../../blog/posts/2025-07-26-numpy-build-error.rst:16
msgid "`pyproject.toml` に以下のような記述があった。"
msgstr "There was a description like the following in `pyproject.toml`."

#: ../../../blog/posts/2025-07-26-numpy-build-error.rst:23
msgid "この指定は SemVer の仕様に基づき、以下の範囲を意味する。"
msgstr ""
"This designation is based on the SemVer specifications and means the "
"following range."

#: ../../../blog/posts/2025-07-26-numpy-build-error.rst:29
msgid ""
"このとき `poetry install` により、`numpy==1.26.4` が選ばれた。しかし、ビルド済みホイール (.whl) "
"が解決されず、Poetry 経由でのインストール時にソースビルドが開始され、Visual C++ Build Tools の導入等を実施しても `not"
" supporting PEP 517 builds` などのエラーで失敗した。"
msgstr ""
"At this time, `numpy==1.26.4` was selected by `poetry install`. However, the"
" pre-built wheel (.whl) was not resolved, a source build was started when "
"installing via Poetry, and even after installing Visual C++ Build Tools, it "
"failed with an error such as `not supporting PEP 517 builds`."

#: ../../../blog/posts/2025-07-26-numpy-build-error.rst:32
msgid "対応内容"
msgstr "Compatible content"

#: ../../../blog/posts/2025-07-26-numpy-build-error.rst:34
msgid "Poetryの依存定義を以下のように修正："
msgstr "Modify the Poetry dependency definition as follows:"

#: ../../../blog/posts/2025-07-26-numpy-build-error.rst:40
msgid "これにより、Poetryは `numpy==2.2.x` 系のビルド済みバイナリを選択し、ビルド処理が不要となり、エラーが解消した。"
msgstr ""
"As a result, Poetry selected pre-built binaries of the `numpy==2.2.x` "
"series, eliminating the need for a build process and eliminating the error."

#: ../../../blog/posts/2025-07-26-numpy-build-error.rst:43
msgid "背景と考察"
msgstr "Background and considerations"

#: ../../../blog/posts/2025-07-26-numpy-build-error.rst:45
msgid ""
"Poetryは `pyproject.toml` の内容や `poetry.lock` "
"に基づき依存を解決するが、場合によってはビルド処理を行うパッケージを選択することがある。"
msgstr ""
"Poetry resolves dependencies based on the contents of `pyproject.toml` and "
"`poetry.lock`, but in some cases it may choose a package to perform the "
"build process."

#: ../../../blog/posts/2025-07-26-numpy-build-error.rst:46
msgid "`numpy` 1.26系は、バイナリを配布していた時期はあったはずだが、現状はバイナリ配布がないようで、ビルドが発生。"
msgstr ""
"There must have been a time when `numpy` 1.26 series distributed binaries, "
"but currently it seems that there is no binary distribution, so a build "
"occurs."

#: ../../../blog/posts/2025-07-26-numpy-build-error.rst:47
msgid "`numpy` 2.2系はホイール配布も安定しており、特にWindows環境ではビルドなしで導入できるケースが多い。"
msgstr ""
"`numpy` 2.2 series has stable wheel distribution, and in many cases it can "
"be installed without building, especially in Windows environments."

#: ../../../blog/posts/2025-07-26-numpy-build-error.rst:48
msgid "`^1.26.0` のような記述は保守的であるが、状況によっては逆に問題を引き起こすこともある。"
msgstr ""
"Although a description like `^1.26.0` is conservative, it can actually cause"
" problems depending on the situation."

#: ../../../blog/posts/2025-07-26-numpy-build-error.rst:51
msgid "今後の教訓"
msgstr "Lessons for the future"

#: ../../../blog/posts/2025-07-26-numpy-build-error.rst:53
msgid "同様の問題に遭遇した際は、以下の観点で早期に切り分けを行う："
msgstr ""
"When you encounter a similar problem, isolate it early based on the "
"following points:"

#: ../../../blog/posts/2025-07-26-numpy-build-error.rst:55
msgid "PEP 517 ビルドなどのお作法の変更に伴うエラーかどうかを確認"
msgstr ""
"Check whether the error is due to a change in manners such as PEP 517 build."

#: ../../../blog/posts/2025-07-26-numpy-build-error.rst:56
msgid "必要に応じてバージョンを変更し、より新しい安定版を利用する"
msgstr "Change the version if necessary to use a newer stable version"

#: ../../../blog/posts/2025-07-26-numpy-build-error.rst:59
msgid "補足：`numpy` の非互換について"
msgstr "Supplement: Regarding `numpy` incompatibility"

#: ../../../blog/posts/2025-07-26-numpy-build-error.rst:61
msgid ""
"`numpy==2.0.0` 以降では、一部破壊的変更が入っているため、依存する他ライブラリとの互換性に注意。必要に応じて `>=1.26,<2.0` "
"のような上限制約も有効。"
msgstr ""
"Since `numpy==2.0.0` contains some breaking changes, be careful about "
"compatibility with other dependent libraries. Upper constraints such as "
"`>=1.26,<2.0` are also valid if necessary."

